<p>Location:</p>
<ul>
  <li>
    <p><strong>Absolute</strong>: A location can be absolute (specific) as in coordinates of a map using longitude and latitude</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p><strong>Relative</strong>: A location can be relative - examples: next door, nearby, a short drive, down the road a ways. Or, it can be in the same general location as another location - example: next to the post office.</p>
  </li>
</ul>
